  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Morbimortality in older patients undergoing abdominal surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      the investigor will register the morbimotality after 6 months of follow up, in patient older
      than 65 year old using the CRISTAL score modify, undergoing abdominal surgery. The measure
      the investigators are using are: Barthel scale, Frail score, Mininutritional score,
      Clavien-Dindo modify, frailty.

      The objective of the study is to predict morbimortality with Cristal score modify
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
